            <!-- [Each of the following three letters is headed with an engraving in brown and white containing tents, 
            	an American flag, a soldier, an American eagle and a buffalo with "Indiana."  inscribed below it.] -->
            
            <div1 type="letter" id="d3">
            	<pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0051"/>
            	<head>James Huntley to Brother <date value="1863-05-02">May the 2nd 1863</date></head>
            
            <opener>
            <dateline>
            <name type="place">Battery Cameron<lb/>
            Washington D C</name><lb/>
            <date value="1863-05-02">May the 2<hi rend="super">nd</hi> 1863</date><lb/>
            </dateline>
            	
            <salute>Dear Brother</salute>
            </opener>
            	
            <p>	
            I received your letter the 1<lb/>
            day of may and it found us<lb/>
            bouth in good health
            </p>
            <p>
            I suppose that there was a plenty<lb/>
            of girls to go a maying with<lb/>
            this year but there is not need of<lb/>
            it out this way for the grass<lb/>
            is five or six inches high here<lb/>
            in the fields <del hand="author" rend="line-through">al</del> and the apples<lb/>
            and peach trees are in bloom
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0052" n="[page 2]"/>
            	
            and the trees is all leiving <!--[leafing]--><lb/> 
            out and the woods is full<lb/>
            of flowers it is indeed very<lb/>
            plesant here for the month<lb/>
            of May The News is here in<lb/>
            the papers that old Jo Hooker<lb/>
            is accrost the river and fighting<lb/>
            he is having a pretty hard time<lb/>
            but i guess that he will do<lb/>
            something yet or i hope so
            </p>
            <p>
            the 6 Maine has lost 6 Killed<lb/>
            and 8 wounded but i don't know<lb/>
            who they wer it has bin as<lb/>
            hot here to day as it was any<lb/>
            day last July down home and<lb/>
            we have bin out on battalion<lb/>
            drill and had a good time to<lb/>
            our extra pay is due now for<lb/>
            a spell but i guess not a great<lb/>
            while they paid us off last<lb/>
            Wedensday and i am going to<lb/>
            send home<del hand="author" rend="line-through">d</del> 20 dollers to mother<lb/>
            and you may put this out for
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0053" n="[page 3]"/>
            	
            for her if you please or<lb/>
            let James Halbot have it<lb/>
            to help pay for the plice <!--[place]--><lb/>
            just as you think best and<lb/>
            if you want any of it<lb/>
            you Can have it
            </p>
            <p>
            they paid us 4 months<lb/>
            pay this and they say that<lb/>
            they will pay us again this<lb/>
            month but i don't know<lb/>
            how it will bee
            </p>
            <p>	
            Oh by the way you did<lb/>
            not say weather you get that<lb/>
            picture that i sent you before<lb/>
            that one that i sent to<lb/> 
            Friend did you get it or not<lb/>
            if you did not get it i will make<lb/>
            you another one as soon as<lb/>
            i go to the City again<lb/>
            i had <del hand="author" rend="line-through">[letter scratched out]</del> 2 letters last night<lb/>
            and i <!--[1]--> night before and i have<lb/>
            got to answer them all<lb/>
            to night if i can get time
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0054" n="[page 4]"/>
            	
            times is dull and i am<lb/>
            in a hurry now and i must<lb/>
            leave you this time but<lb/>
            will write you again
            </p>
            	
            <closer>	
            <salute>this is from your
            brother</salute>
            <signed>James <unclear>[-]</unclear> Huntley</signed>
            </closer>
            	
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
